The only concrete deployment artifact here is the implementation source, but there’s one exploitable wrinkle: because it’s upgradeable, the implementation may itself be uninitialized. I’m checking whether enough on-chain addresses are recoverable locally to initialize that instance honestly and still drive the original stale-depositor flow.
